<Section title="Stress">
The internal forces and moments generally vary from point to point. Obtaining this distribution is of primary importance in mechanics of materials. The total force in a cross-section, divided by the cross-sectional area, is the <strong>stress</strong>. We use stress to <strong>normalize forces</strong> with respect to the size of the geometry.



</Section>

