<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress-Figures/Shear Stress.png" width="2"> Shear stress</Image>

 Obtained when transverse forces are applied to a member. The distribution of shear stresses cannot be assumed uniform. Common in bolts, pins and rivets used to connect various structural members.

<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress-Figures/Avg Shear Stress.png" width="4"> Average shear stress</Image>

<DisplayEquation equation="\\tau_{ave} = \\frac{V}{A}\\" />

 where <InlineEquation equation="V" /> is the internal resultant shear force and <InlineEquation equation="A" /> is the cross-sectional area of the bar where the shear stress <InlineEquation equation="\\tau_{ave}" /> is calculated.




 <strong>Example:</strong> Single Shear
Determine the shear stress in the bolt.

<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress-Figures/SingleShear.png" width="2.5"> Single shear stress</Image>

<DisplayEquation equation="\\tau_{ave} = \\frac{P}{A}\\" />
 <strong>*Expandable derivation*</strong>
<DisplayEquation equation="\\Sigma F_y = V-P = 0\\" />
<DisplayEquation equation="V = P\\" />

 <strong>**End Derivation**</strong>

 <strong>Example:</strong> Double Shear

Determine the shear stress in the bolt.

<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress-Figures/DoubleShear.png" width="2.5"> Double shear stress</Image>

<DisplayEquation equation="\\tau_{ave} = \\frac{P}{2A}\\" />

<strong>*Expandable derivation*</strong>
<DisplayEquation equation="\\Sigma F_y = 2V-P = 0\\" />
<DisplayEquation equation="V = \\frac{P}{2}\\" />

 <strong>**End Derivation**</strong>

